This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the bias-variance tradeoff in neural networks. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural networks are a popular tool in AI research. Additionally, the paper mentions empirical results with over-parameterized neural networks, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper introduces a new decomposition of variance, which could also make it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
